This paper deals with object pose estimation using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper involves the use of graph convolutional neural networks (GCNNs) for mesh reconstruction, which is a technique commonly used in robotics (cs.RO). The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for pose estimation, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves the use of geometric techniques for pose estimation, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.GR).
